<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dispossess" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dispossess,</orth> to deprive of possession: <cit><quote>d. the soul of thy grandam,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 4.2.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. IV, 2, 64</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to d. that child,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 1.131" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 131</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.139" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 139</bibl>. With <emph>of</emph> == to deprive of: <bibl n="shak. mm 2.4.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 4, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 23</bibl>.
